<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-03-22T11:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-03-22T11:45:00-05:00" n="415" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d415">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/3043: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ramer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-03-22T11:00:00-05:45"><hi rend="italic">March 22,
                                        1924—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 6:35
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>44. The Department’s 30 March 18, 7 p.m. A note from Nicaraguan
                            Government states that it not only does not object to the use of marines
                            at Chinandega but at this time expresses its consent to similar action
                            in any other analogous case.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Ramer</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>